name: Retrieve current config details
xml: <get-resource plugin='org.onap.ccsdk.sli.adaptors.resource.sql.SqlResource' resource='SQL' key="SELECT service_description, vnf_name, vm_name, vnf_type, vnfc_type, host_ip_address FROM UPLOAD_CONFIG WHERE vnf_id = $input.action-identifiers.vnf-id AND config_indicator='Current' AND (pending_delete IS NULL OR pending_delete != 'Y')" pfx="currnt-config[]">

name: return failure
xml:
<return status='failure'>
<parameter name='error-code' value='401'/>
<parameter name='error-message' value="`$error-message`"/>
<parameter name='output.status.code' value='401'/>
<parameter name='output.status.message' value="`$error-message`"/>

name: Set error message
xml:
<set>
<parameter name='error-message' value="`'Current configuration not found in the repository for vnf-id: ' + $input.action-identifiers.vnf-id`"/>

name: Set error message
xml:
<set>
<parameter name='error-message' value="`'Error while retrieving current configuration from the repository for the vnf-id : ' + $input.action-identifiers.vnf-id`"/>

name: Set context
xml:
<set>
<parameter name='service-description' value="`$currnt-config[$i].service-description`" />
<parameter name='vm-name' value="`$currnt-config[$i].vm-name`" />
<parameter name='vnf-type' value="`$currnt-config[$i].vnf-type`" />
<parameter name='vnfc-type' value="`$currnt-config[$i].vnfc-type`" />
<parameter name='host-ip-address' value="`$currnt-config[$i].host-ip-address`" />
<parameter name='vnf-name' value="`$currnt-config[$i].vnf-name`" />

name: Mark current configs as historic
xml: <update resource='SQL' force='true' plugin='org.onap.ccsdk.sli.adaptors.resource.sql.SqlResource' key="UPDATE UPLOAD_CONFIG SET config_indicator=null WHERE vnf_id = $input.action-identifiers.vnf-id AND config_indicator='Current' AND (pending_delete IS NULL OR pending_delete != 'Y')">

name: Store device config as 'Current'
xml: <save plugin='org.onap.ccsdk.sli.adaptors.resource.sql.SqlResource' resource='SQL' key="INSERT INTO UPLOAD_CONFIG (request_id, originator_id, service_description, action, vnf_id, vnf_name, vm_name, vnf_type, vnfc_type, host_ip_address, config_indicator, content) SELECT request_id, originator_id, service_description, action, vnf_id, vnf_name, vm_name, vnf_type, vnfc_type, host_ip_address, 'Current', content FROM UPLOAD_CONFIG WHERE vnf_id = $input.action-identifiers.vnf-id AND config_indicator = 'Running' AND (pending_delete IS NULL OR pending_delete != 'Y')" force='true'>

name: Set error message
xml:
<set>
<parameter name='error-message' value='DG to retrieve running configuration not found'/>

name: Set error message
xml:
<set>
<parameter name='error-message' value="`'Error while marking current configuration as historic in the repository for vnf-id:' + $input.action-identifiers.vnf-id`" />

name: Set error message
xml:
<set>
<parameter name='error-message' value="`'Error while storing the new current configuration in the repository for vnf-id: ' + $input.action-identifiers.vnf-id`" />

name: return failure
xml:
<return status='failure'>
<parameter name='error-code' value='401'/>
<parameter name='error-message' value="`$error-message`"/>
<parameter name='output.status.code' value='401'/>
<parameter name='output.status.message' value="`$error-message`"/>
